rComments: I LOVED Prof Delgado! I took His128 over the summer and was BLOWN away by the knowledge this woman has. I learned a ton and I would gladly take her again. Not a slack class, be prepared to read a ton but the material is relevant and she connects it all with her lectures. She respects her material and you should too if you want to do well.

I loved this professor. To be honest, I wasn't even interested in the subject matter, but her enthusiasm draws you in. I won't lie, she asks a lot of you, but in the end it's a rewarding experience. If you're the kind of person who is in college just to get a degree, then take someone else. If you want to learn and grow, take Delgado.

One of best lecturers, great clear and strong voice.  Essay quiz every single Thursday! (Prompt given a day before test) Assigns way too much reading and somewhat treats this like an upper division history class

Amazing Professor!! Great lecturer and clear on what she wants from students. There is a good amount of reading for this class. There were quizzes&2 reading responses worthy a good amount but we're very much do-able if you just read. I honestly learned so much and would take a class taught by her again. Always willing to make time for students.
